body:
[`syslog.Dial`](https://github.com/golang/go/blob/master/src/log/syslog/syslog.go#L115) and `syslog.New` take a `syslog.Priority` as an argument and stores it in a field named `priority`. This field is used exactly twice:
 - as a syslog _facility_  in [`writeAndRetry`](https://github.com/golang/go/blob/master/src/log/syslog/syslog.go#L245)
 - as the syslog priority in [`Writer.Write`](https://golang.org/src/log/syslog/syslog.go#L171)

For examples of someone confused by this in the wild, check out  [`logrus_syslog`](https://github.com/Sirupsen/logrus/blob/master/hooks/syslog/syslog.go#L22) or [`golang-samples`](https://github.com/golang-samples/log/blob/master/syslog/main.go#L9), which thinks that creating a syslog writer with a severity instead of a facility will do something meaningful:

```
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"log/syslog"
)

func test(p syslog.Priority, msg string) {
	w, e := syslog.New(p, msg)
	if e != nil {
		fmt.Println("Error opening syslog", e)
	} else {
		w.Debug("hello, world")
	}
}

func main() {
	test(syslog.LOG_ERR, "ALEX")
	test(syslog.LOG_INFO, "BEN")
	test(syslog.LOG_DAEMON, "CAROLE")
	test(syslog.LOG_USER, "DOUG")
}
```

```
<7>1 2016-05-18T10:50:43.326575-07:00 ubuntu-16 ALEX 2517 - -  hello, world
<7>1 2016-05-18T10:50:43.327090-07:00 ubuntu-16 BEN 2517 - -  hello, world
<31>1 2016-05-18T10:50:43.327409-07:00 ubuntu-16 CAROLE 2517 - -  hello, world
<15>1 2016-05-18T10:50:43.327707-07:00 ubuntu-16 DOUG 2517 - -  hello, world
```

It would be great if facility was a different type from priority, but barring that it would be wonderful to update the documentation here. In particular, I would love to see `syslog.New` and `syslog.Dial` take a variable named _facility_ and explain the difference, with an example usage.

I'm happy to do it if such a change could be merged. I see that the package is "frozen" -- will it still accept doc fixes?
